Calibrate camera¶

In [2]:
camera = Camera()
camera.calibrate(nx=9,ny=6, path_pattern="camera_cal/*.jpg")
#camera.load_calibration("camera_cal/calibration_info.p")

# show example
src_img = mpimg.imread("camera_cal/calibration1.jpg")
dst_img = camera.undistort(src_img)
f, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(24, 9))
f.tight_layout()
ax1.imshow(src_img)
ax1.set_title('Original Image', fontsize=50)
ax2.imshow(dst_img)
ax2.set_title('Undistorted Image', fontsize=50)
plt.subplots_adjust(left=0., right=1, top=0.9, bottom=0.)
f.savefig("output_images/undistort_img.jpg")

Generate perspective transform¶

In [5]:
src_filename="test_images/straight_lines1.jpg"
src_pts, dst_pts = camera.generate_perspective_transform(src_filename)
src_pts = [tuple(x) for x in src_pts]
dst_pts = [tuple(x) for x in dst_pts]
print(src_pts)
print(dst_pts)
#draw points on test image
img = mpimg.imread(src_filename)
undist = camera.undistort(img)
warped = camera.warp(undist)
cv2.line(undist, src_pts[0], src_pts[1], (255,0,0), 5)
cv2.line(undist, src_pts[1], src_pts[2], (255,0,0), 5)
cv2.line(undist, src_pts[2], src_pts[3], (255,0,0), 5)
cv2.line(undist, src_pts[3], src_pts[0], (255,0,0), 5)
cv2.line(warped, dst_pts[0], dst_pts[1], (255,0,0), 5)
cv2.line(warped, dst_pts[1], dst_pts[2], (255,0,0), 5)
cv2.line(warped, dst_pts[2], dst_pts[3], (255,0,0), 5)
cv2.line(warped, dst_pts[3], dst_pts[0], (255,0,0), 5)
f, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(24, 9))
f.tight_layout()
ax1.imshow(undist)
ax1.set_title('Undistorted image with source points drawn', fontsize=25)
ax2.imshow(warped)
ax2.set_title('Warped result with destination points drawn', fontsize=25)
plt.subplots_adjust(left=0., right=1, top=0.9, bottom=0.)
f.savefig("output_images/warped_straight_lines.jpg")

Searching lane line pixels and fitting a polynomial function¶

In [7]:
from src.line import Line
from src.basic_blind_search import BasicBlindSearch
import numpy as np
binary_warped = camera.warp(binary_img)
ym_per_pix = 30/720 # meters per pixel in y dimension
xm_per_pix = 3.7/700 # meters per pixel in x dimension
L = Line(xm_per_pix, ym_per_pix)
R = Line(xm_per_pix, ym_per_pix)
blind_search = BasicBlindSearch()
L.allx, L.ally, R.allx, R.ally = blind_search.search(binary_warped)
# Generates y values for plotting
ploty = np.linspace(0, binary_warped.shape[0]-1, binary_warped.shape[0] )
L.fit_polynomial(ploty)
R.fit_polynomial(ploty)
color_warp = np.dstack((binary_warped, binary_warped, binary_warped))
L.draw(color_warp, [255,0,0])
R.draw(color_warp, [0,0,255])
plt.plot(L.current_plotx, ploty, color='green')
plt.plot(R.current_plotx, ploty, color='green')
plt.imshow(color_warp)
plt.savefig("output_images/color_fit_lines.jpg")

Result plotted back down onto the road¶

In [8]:
from src.lines_detector import LinesDetector
detector = LinesDetector(camera)
# Update the average values for each line
L.update(ploty)
R.update(ploty)
detector.L = L
detector.R = R
detector.ploty = ploty
detector.sanity_check(binary_warped)
result = detector.draw_lane(dst_img, binary_warped)
plt.imshow(result)
plt.savefig("output_images/example_output.jpg")
